// Design Editor Store
// Zustand store for the design editor UI state (ported from open-pencil Vue reactive store).
// Non-serializable engine objects (SceneGraph, SkiaRenderer, UndoManager, CanvasKit, TextEditor)
// live as module-level singletons in designEditorRefs.ts; this store holds only serializable state.
//
// STATE SHAPE:
//   activeTool           - Tool enum (SELECT | FRAME | SECTION | RECTANGLE | ELLIPSE | LINE | POLYGON | STAR | TEXT | PEN | HAND)
//   currentPageId        - ID of the active page node in the scene graph
//   panX, panY           - Canvas pan offset in screen pixels
//   zoom                 - Canvas zoom factor (0.02 – 256)
//   pageColor            - Background color of the canvas page
//   showUI               - Whether the design UI chrome is visible
//   selectedIds          - Set of selected node IDs
//   hoveredNodeId        - Node currently under cursor (or null)
//   editingTextId        - Node currently being edited as text (or null)
//   marquee              - Current rubber-band selection rect (or null)
//   snapGuides           - Array of active snap guides
//   rotationPreview      - { nodeId, angle } during rotation drag (or null)
//   dropTargetId         - Node ID being hovered as a drop target (or null)
//   layoutInsertIndicator - Visual indicator for auto-layout insert position (or null)
//   penState             - Active pen tool path state: vertices, segments, dragTangent, closingToFirst
//   penCursorX/Y         - Live cursor position for pen preview
//   remoteCursors        - Multiplayer: array of { name, color, x, y, selection? }
//   renderVersion        - Incremented to trigger Skia repaint (does NOT save to MCP)
//   sceneVersion         - Incremented to trigger both repaint AND auto-save
//   contextMenu          - Screen position of context menu (or null)
//
// INTERNAL HELPERS (module-private, not exposed on state):
//   runLayoutForNode     - Re-runs computeLayout on the node and all auto-layout ancestors
//   syncIfInsideComponent - Walks up to find a COMPONENT ancestor and calls syncInstances on it

---

FUNCTION runLayoutForNode(id) [private]
  Get the node from the graph. If it has an auto-layout mode, run computeLayout on it.
  Walk up through parentId chain, running computeLayout on each auto-layout ancestor.

---

FUNCTION syncIfInsideComponent(nodeId) [private]
  Walk up through parentId chain. If any ancestor is a COMPONENT, call graph.syncInstances on it and return.

---

FUNCTION requestRender()
  Increment both renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION requestRepaint()
  Increment only renderVersion (no save trigger).

---

FUNCTION setTool(tool)
  Set activeTool.

---

FUNCTION select(ids, additive)
  IF additive: toggle each id in selectedIds (add if absent, remove if present).
  ELSE: replace selectedIds with a new Set of the given ids.

---

FUNCTION clearSelection()
  Set selectedIds to an empty Set.

---

FUNCTION selectAll()
  Get all direct children of currentPageId from the graph. Set selectedIds to their ids.

---

FUNCTION setMarquee(rect)
  Set marquee and increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION setSnapGuides(guides)
  Set snapGuides and increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION setRotationPreview(preview)
  Set rotationPreview and increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION setHoveredNode(id)
  If id already equals hoveredNodeId, return early (no re-render).
  Else set hoveredNodeId and increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION setDropTarget(id)
  Set dropTargetId and increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION setLayoutInsertIndicator(indicator)
  Set layoutInsertIndicator and increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION updateNode(id, changes)
  Apply changes to the node in the graph.
  If changes include vectorNetwork, invalidate the renderer's vector path cache for id.
  Run layout and component sync.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION updateNodeWithUndo(id, changes, label)
  Snapshot the current values of all changed keys from the node.
  Apply changes to the graph node.
  If changes include vectorNetwork, invalidate vector path cache.
  Run layout and component sync.
  Push an undo entry: forward re-applies changes, inverse restores snapshot.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION commitNodeUpdate(id, previous, label)
  Snapshot the current values of all keys in previous (from the live node).
  Push an undo entry: forward applies the current snapshot, inverse applies previous.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.
  NOTE: Used after the node has already been mutated (e.g., after drag/resize ends).

---

FUNCTION createShape(type, x, y, w, h, parentId)
  Look up the default fill for type from DEFAULT_FILLS.
  Create the node in the graph under parentId (or currentPageId).
  Apply special overrides: SECTION gets stroke+cornerRadius, POLYGON gets pointCount=3,
    STAR gets pointCount=5 and starInnerRadius=0.38.
  Snapshot the created node. Run layout and component sync.
  Push an undo entry: forward recreates the node, inverse deletes it and removes from selection.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.
  Return the new node's id.

---

FUNCTION deleteSelected()
  For each id in selectedIds: snapshot the node's type, parentId, index in parent's childIds, and data.
  If nothing to delete, return.
  Delete all selected nodes from the graph.
  Push an undo entry: forward deletes them again and clears selection, inverse recreates each node
    in reverse order at their original parent+index and restores selection.
  Clear selectedIds. Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION duplicateSelected()
  For each selected node: create a copy shifted +20,+20 with name appended ' copy'.
  Push an undo entry: forward recreates copies, inverse deletes them.
  Select the new copies. Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION undoAction()
  Call undo.undo(). Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION redoAction()
  Call undo.redo(). Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION commitMove(originals)
  Capture final positions of all nodes in the originals Map.
  Sync component instances for all moved nodes.
  Push an undo entry: forward applies finals, inverse applies originals.

---

FUNCTION commitResize(nodeId, origRect)
  Capture final rect {x, y, width, height} from the live node.
  Sync component instances.
  Push an undo entry: forward applies finalRect, inverse applies origRect.

---

FUNCTION commitRotation(nodeId, origRotation)
  Capture final rotation from the live node.
  Sync component instances.
  Push an undo entry: forward applies finalRotation, inverse applies origRotation.

---

FUNCTION startTextEditing(nodeId)
  If another node is being edited, commit that first.
  Get the node. If textEditor and renderer are available, call textEditor.setRenderer + textEditor.start.
  Set editingTextId. Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION commitTextEdit()
  If textEditor is not active, clear editingTextId and return.
  Call textEditor.stop() to get { nodeId, text }.
  Apply the new text to the graph node.
  If text changed: push an undo entry for the text change.
  Clear editingTextId. Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION groupSelected()
  Get selected nodes. All must share the same parent.
  Compute bounding box of all selected nodes using absolute positions.
  Create a GROUP node at (minX, minY) sized (width, height) inside the parent.
  Insert the group at the position of the first selected node in parent.childIds.
  Reparent all selected nodes into the group.
  Push an undo entry: forward recreates the group and reparents, inverse dissolves the group.
  Select the group. Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION ungroupSelected()
  The selected node must be a GROUP.
  For each child of the group: reparent it to the group's parent, inserting at the group's original index.
  Delete the group.
  Push an undo entry: forward re-dissolves, inverse recreates the group.
  Select the former children. Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION bringToFront()
  For each selected node: move it to the end of its parent's childIds.
  Push an undo entry capturing original and final child orders per parent.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION sendToBack()
  For each selected node: move it to the front (unshift) of its parent's childIds.
  Push an undo entry capturing original and final child orders per parent.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION setLayoutMode(id, mode)
  Snapshot layout-related fields on the node.
  Apply the new layoutMode. If switching from NONE to auto-layout, reset spacing/padding to 0 and sizing to HUG.
  Run computeLayout if mode is not NONE. Run layout for ancestors.
  Snapshot final state. Push an undo entry.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION penAddVertex(x, y)
  If penState is null, initialize it with the first vertex at (x, y).
  Else if there are more than 2 vertices and cursor is within 8px of the first vertex: auto-close by calling penCommit(true).
  Else append the new vertex and a segment from the previous vertex with the current dragTangent.
  Reset dragTangent to null. Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION penSetDragTangent(tx, ty)
  Set penState.dragTangent to (tx, ty).
  Also update the tangentEnd of the last segment to (-tx, -ty) for smooth bezier curves.
  Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION penSetClosingToFirst(closing)
  Set penState.closingToFirst. Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION penCommit(closed)
  If penState has fewer than 2 vertices, cancel (clear penState and tool).
  Build a VectorNetwork from vertices and segments. If closed, add a region with NONZERO winding.
  Normalize vertex coordinates to be relative to the bounding box origin.
  Create a VECTOR node at the bounding box position with the normalized network.
  Apply fills for closed paths, strokes for open paths.
  Push an undo entry: forward recreates the vector node, inverse deletes it.
  Clear penState, reset tool to SELECT, select the new node.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION penCancel()
  Clear penState, penCursorX/Y. Reset activeTool to SELECT. Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION isTopLevel(parentId)
  Return true if parentId is null, the graph root, or the currentPageId.

---

FUNCTION reparentNodes(nodeIds, newParentId)
  For each node: skip SECTIONs being placed inside non-CANVAS/SECTION parents.
  Reparent qualifying nodes to newParentId (graph handles coordinate transform).
  Push an undo entry: forward reparents to new parent with final positions, inverse restores originals.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION reorderInAutoLayout(nodeId, parentId, insertIndex)
  If node is in a different parent, convert its absolute position to the new parent's local space and reparent.
  Reorder the node to insertIndex inside parentId. Run computeLayout and layout for the parent.
  Push an undo entry: forward applies final order+position, inverse restores original parent/order/position.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION adoptNodesIntoSection(sectionId)
  Find all sibling nodes that are fully contained within the section's bounding box.
  Reparent each such sibling into the section.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION applyZoom(delta, centerX, centerY)
  Compute new zoom as current * ZOOM_SENSITIVITY^delta, clamped to [0.02, 256].
  Adjust panX/panY so the point under (centerX, centerY) stays fixed.
  Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION pan(dx, dy)
  Add dx to panX, dy to panY. Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION screenToCanvas(sx, sy)
  Return { x: (sx - panX) / zoom, y: (sy - panY) / zoom }.

---

FUNCTION initFromGraph()
  Get the root node from the graph. Set currentPageId to root's first child.
  Run computeAllLayouts to apply auto-layout positioning for MCP-created designs.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion. Clear selection.

---

FUNCTION zoomToFit(viewportWidth, viewportHeight)
  If the page has no children: fit to the page frame itself with 40px padding, cap zoom at 1.
  Else compute the bounding box of all children plus the page frame.
  Compute zoom to fit with 60px padding, capped at 2x.
  Set zoom and pan so content is centered in the viewport.
  Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION setContextMenu(menu)
  Set contextMenu to the given { x, y } or null.

---

FUNCTION alignNodes(direction)
  Requires at least 2 selected nodes.
  Compute the union bounding box of all selected nodes using absolute positions.
  For each node, compute the local offset (abs - local) and apply the alignment formula:
    left → minX, centerH → center, right → maxX - width,
    top → minY, centerV → center, bottom → maxY - height.
  Snapshot originals and finals. Push an undo entry.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION distributeNodes(axis)
  Requires at least 3 selected nodes.
  Sort nodes by their absolute position along the axis.
  Distribute evenly between the first and last node's outer edges.
  Snapshot originals and finals. Push an undo entry.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION flipSelected(axis)
  Compute bounding box of all selected nodes using absolute positions.
  For horizontal: mirror each node's x across the center of the bounding box.
  For vertical: mirror each node's y across the center of the bounding box.
  Snapshot originals and finals. Push an undo entry.
  Increment renderVersion and sceneVersion.

---

FUNCTION zoomToSelection(viewportWidth, viewportHeight)
  Compute bounding box of all selected nodes using absolute positions.
  Compute zoom to fit selection with 60px padding, capped at 2x.
  Set zoom and pan so selection is centered in the viewport.
  Increment renderVersion.

---

FUNCTION getSelectedNodes()                                             EXPORT
  Return a copy of each node in selectedIds from the graph.

---

FUNCTION getSelectedNode()                                              EXPORT
  Return the single selected node if exactly one is selected; otherwise undefined.

---

FUNCTION getLayerTree()                                                 EXPORT
  Call graph.flattenTree(currentPageId) and return the result.

---

// Store is exported as useDesignEditorStore (Zustand hook).
